This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with host-based intrusion detection. It also involves the use of generative adversarial networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
